verses.verse: A <S%H7892>Song<s%> of <S%H4609>degrees<s%>. Unto thee lift I <S%H5375>up<s%> mine <S%H5869>eyes<s%>, O thou that <S%H3427>dwellest<s%> in the <S%H8064>heavens<s%>.

Behold, as the <S%H5869>eyes<s%> of <S%H5650>servants<s%> look unto the <S%H3027>hand<s%> of their <S%H113>masters<s%>, and as the <S%H5869>eyes<s%> of a <S%H8198>maiden<s%> unto the <S%H3027>hand<s%> of her <S%H1404>mistress<s%>; so our <S%H5869>eyes<s%> wait upon the <S%H3068>LORD<s%> our <S%H430>God<s%>, until that he have <S%H2603>mercy<s%> upon us.
Have <S%H2603>mercy<s%> upon us, O <S%H3068>LORD<s%>, have <S%H2603>mercy<s%> upon us: for we are <S%H7227>exceedingly<s%> <S%H7646>filled<s%> with <S%H937>contempt<s%>.

Our <S%H5315>soul<s%> is <S%H7227>exceedingly<s%> <S%H7646>filled<s%> with the <S%H3933>scorning<s%> of those that are at <S%H7600>ease<s%>, and with the <S%H937>contempt<s%> of the <S%H3238%H1343%H1349>proud<s%>.
